      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HE'S REGAL (1) is yet to be beaten at the course and distance, scoring four wins from as many starts. Placed last time (19.87) at Capalaba in a Grade 4/5, finishing third and beaten a nose. Looks the one to beat with even luck. RUIN ART (6) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 2.75 lengths into third (25.38) at this track in a Grade 5 over 457m. Must be included in calculations. RED HOT PENNY (2) was never in contention last time after being shuffled back early at this track, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Rockhampton (29.81) beating Zipping Gatsby in a Grade 5/6 on March 1. Goes very well from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from six starts. One of the better hopes. MANILA PHANTOM (7) is worth including after a top-three finish at this track and distance most recently.",
